cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper deals with a computer vision task of baggage ReID and proposes a novel dataset named MVB for the same. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of a merged Siamese network as a baseline model, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the security aspect of baggage ReID, which falls under the category of cryptography and security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another likely category. Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques to handle pose variation and occlusion, which falls under the category of information retrieval. Hence, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category.
